OL,3,CUK marks national Covid-19 day of
OL,4,Creflection six years on from pandemic
OL,6,FBaroness Morgan, chairwoman of the UK
OL,7,FCommission on Covid Commemoration,
OL,8,Fsaid: "For so many across the country,
OL,9,Fthe Covid-19 pandemic left a legacy of
OL,10,Fgrief and loss that is still carried
OL,11,Ftoday. Everyone lost something.
OL,13,F"This year's Covid-19 day of
OL,14,Freflection is an opportunity for us
OL,15,Fall to pause and remember the lives
OL,16,Flost because of the pandemic,
OL,17,Frecognising the efforts and sacrifices
OL,18,Fof frontline workers, as well as the
OL,19,Fvolunteering and community spirit we
OL,20,Fsaw and the contribution of the
OL,21,Fscientific community."
OL,26,@pD@GOUuD@AOU}D@VO]
